accessibility.text: 1. Listening Session - Lets listen to music that we love and talk about it!
2. Musical Analysis - After the listening session, we will discuss the music and try to pick it apart.
3. What is Rhythm? - Main topic for this lesson.
4. Emotional Context - Section diving into how differences in rhythm can affect our emotions while listening to music.
4.1. Breaking down stereotypes and biases associated with rhythm.
5. Rhythm Exercises - Hands-on activities centered around the topic of rhythm in music.

Options (adaptable): Play with the Noise and Buttons app, Watch videos about rhythm, Try some rhythm patterns, Analyze more music and either talk about, write about, or sketch about findings and emotions associated with rhythm.
6. Musical Playtime - Time to mess around with musical instruments and software, create original music, or listen to music.
